        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-01-28 14:04:34.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\nAre you planning on adding another implementation of the AAIResourcesClient to the code? Why are there so many interfaces and layers around it?",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "6548e79532a706255e5c32f36d687cc61a6b058c",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2815,
          "name": "Michal Kabaj",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "michal.kabaj@nokia.com",
          "username": "kabayashi"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-01-29 09:46:33.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nHi Max, No, we are definitely not planning on adding any new AAi client implementations, just reusing what is mostly already there :)\nThis change is still a draft and is not yet final. I don't exactly understand what you mean by \"so many interfaces and layers\" - nothing new has been added with this change, only reused and we intend to further simplify it without breaking the interface segregation principle.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "c1efff8646f4dde7c460c3954d7bd32750192e27",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 97,
          "name": "Max Benjamin",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "max.benjamin@att.com",
          "username": "mfour"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-01-29 16:09:28.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Hi Max, No, we are definitely not planning on adding any new AAi\n > client implementations, just reusing what is mostly already there\n > :)\n > This change is still a draft and is not yet final. I don't exactly\n > understand what you mean by \"so many interfaces and layers\" -\n > nothing new has been added with this change, only reused and we\n > intend to further simplify it without breaking the interface\n > segregation principle.\n\nWe have an interface segregation which is the client itself. I'm not sure we need another set of interfaces on top of it.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
